'''Windows 10'''是[[微軟|微軟]]於2015年推出的[[Windows_NT|Windows NT]]内核[[作業系統|作業系統]]，為[[Windows_8.1|Windows 8.1]]的後繼者。設計目標是統一包括個人電腦、平板電腦、智能手机、嵌入式系統、[[Xbox_One|Xbox One]]、[[Surface_Hub|Surface Hub]]和[[Microsoft_HoloLens|HoloLens]]等设备的操作系统。根據微軟官方統計，Windows 10的佔有率已經超越Windows 7，在所有Windows中位列第一。<ref>{{Cite_web |url=http://www.ithome.com/html/win10/280068.htm |title=微软统计：2016年8月Win10安装量份额已超越Win7 |date=2016-12-13 |accessdate=2016-12-25 |work=IT之家 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161225145203/http://www.ithome.com/html/win10/280068.htm |archivedate=2016-12-25 }}</ref><ref name="cw-rushed">{{cite web|url=http://www.computerworld.com/article/2953307/microsoft-windows/windows-10-is-for-suckers.html|title=Windows 10 is for suckers|accessdate=2015-09-03|date=2015-07-28|last=Horowitz|first=Michael|work=Computerworld|publisher=IDG|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150903023515/http://www.computerworld.com/article/2953307/microsoft-windows/windows-10-is-for-suckers.html|archivedate=2015-09-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/3073457/windows/how-microsofts-nasty-new-windows-10-pop-up-tricks-you-into-upgrading.html|title=How Microsoft's tricky new Windows 10 pop-up deceives you into upgrading|date=2016-05-22|last=Chacos|first=Brad|work=[[PC_World|PC World]]|publisher=[[IDG|IDG]]|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716011026/http://www.pcworld.com/article/3073457/windows/how-microsofts-nasty-new-windows-10-pop-up-tricks-you-into-upgrading.html|archivedate=2016-07-16|accessdate=2016-11-27}}</ref>

Windows 10引入「[[通用Windows平台|通用Windows平台]]」（UWP），并扩充了[[Modern_UI|Modern UI]]风格的应用程序，所有运行Windows 10的设备共享一個通用的應用程式架構和Windows商店的生態系統。这些应用程序可以在多种设备上运行——包括PC、平板电脑、智能手机、嵌入式系统、Xbox One、Surface Hub以及HoloLens全息设备。微软還为Windows 10设计一个新的开始菜单，其中包含[[Windows_7|Windows 7]]的传统开始菜单元素与[[Windows_8|Windows 8]]的磁贴。Windows 10还引入一个虚拟桌面系统、一个称为[[任务视图|任务视图]]的工作切換器、[[Microsoft_Edge|Microsoft Edge]]浏览器、支持指纹和-{zh-tw:臉部;zh-hk:面部;zh-hans:面部}-、虹膜识别-{zh-tw:登入;zh-cn:登录;}-、企业环境的新安全功能，以及提高操作系统的游戏图形功能的[[DirectX|DirectX]] 12和[[Windows_Display_Driver_Model|WDDM]] 2.0。<ref name="zdnet-onebillion">{{Cite_web |last1=Bott |first1=Ed |title=Microsoft's big Windows 10 goal: one billion or bust |url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsofts-big-windows-10-goal-one-billion-or-bust/ |website=ZDNet |publisher=CBS Interactive |date=2015-05-08 |accessdate=2015-07-29 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104053107/http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsofts-big-windows-10-goal-one-billion-or-bust/ |archivedate=2017-01-04 }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://gs.statcounter.com/#all-os-ww-monthly-201506-201701|title=Top 8 operating systems from June 2015 to Jan 2017|publisher=StatCounter|access-date=2017-01-01|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120526/http://gs.statcounter.com/%23mobile_browser-ww-monthly-201012-201111-bar#all-os-ww-monthly-201506-201701|archivedate=2012-05-26}}</ref><ref name="desktop">{{cite web|url=http://gs.statcounter.com/os-market-share/desktop/worldwide/#monthly-201506-201701|title=Top 8 desktop OSs from June 2015 to Jan 2017|publisher=StatCounter|access-date=2017-01-01|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170124113625/http://gs.statcounter.com/os-market-share/desktop/worldwide/#monthly-201506-201701|archivedate=2017-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://betanews.com/2016/10/01/wtf-windows-10-losing-share/|title=WTF? Windows 10 now actually losing market share|quote=It was expected, that once Windows 10 stopped being free, upgrades would slow significantly. [..] In September though, according to NetMarketShare, Windows 10 didn’t just show slower growth, it actually went into reverse gear and lost usage share. Yes, you read that right.|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129234522/https://betanews.com/2016/10/01/wtf-windows-10-losing-share/|archivedate=2017-01-29|accessdate=2017-02-11}}</ref>

正式版本於2015年7月29日發行並開放给符合條件的用户免費升級，不過Windows 7、8已於[[UTC-10|UTC-10]]的2016年7月30日零点關閉免費直接升級通道<ref>{{Cite_web |url=http://news.mydrivers.com/1/493/493171.htm |title=Win10免费升级29日结束 中国用户额外多1天：感谢时差 |publisher=驱动之家 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814043022/http://news.mydrivers.com/1/493/493171.htm |archivedate=2016-08-14 |accessdate=2016-07-31 }}</ref>，而面向使用辅助技术的用户而设的Windows 10免费升级亦于2017年12月31日结束<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://scitech.people.com.cn/n1/2017/1108/c1007-29633230.html|title=微软年底停止Win10免费升级|accessdate=2018-03-12|author=科技日报|date=|last=|work=人民网|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312204749/http://scitech.people.com.cn/n1/2017/1108/c1007-29633230.html|archivedate=2018-03-12}}</ref>，之後升级就必须付費（曾經升級過Windows 10並取得數位許可的使用者除外<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/12435/windows-10-upgrade-faq|title=Upgrade to Windows 10: FAQ|accessdate=2017-04-22|author=|date=|publisher=|quote=After you upgrade to Windows 10, you can reinstall or do a clean installation on the same device. You won't need a product key to reactivate Windows 10 on the same hardware.|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421070729/https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/12435/windows-10-upgrade-faq/|archivedate=2017-04-21}}</ref>）。但据消息称，[[Windows_7|Windows 7]]、[[Windows_8|Windows 8]]用户仍可免费升级至 Windows 10，前提是有正版的 Windows -{zh-tw:數位授權;zh-hk:數碼授權;zh-cn:数字许可;}-<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iqmore.tw/2020-windows-7-upgrade-to-windows-10|title=2020年Windows 7照樣免費升級Windows 10，繼續更新保護系統安全|accessdate=2020-05-11|author=老貓 iqmore|date=|last=|work=老貓測3C|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403112714/https://iqmore.tw/2020-windows-7-upgrade-to-windows-10|archivedate=2020-04-03}}</ref>。

