微軟可能將一些預建裝置描述為“認證過”的。認證的平板必須包括電源鍵、音量升降鍵，但並不要求裝置[[Windows键|Win鍵]]和旋轉鎖定鍵<ref name="ndtv-specs">{{Cite_web |title=Windows 10 Minimum Hardware Requirements and Upgrade Paths Detailed |url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/laptops/news/windows-10-minimum-hardware-requirements-and-upgrade-paths-detailed-672319 |website=NDTV |accessdate=2015-03-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321031821/http://gadgets.ndtv.com/laptops/news/windows-10-minimum-hardware-requirements-and-upgrade-paths-detailed-672319 |archivedate=2015-03-21 }}</ref>。如同[[Windows_8|Windows 8]]，所有認證裝置必須將UEFI Secure Boot默認啟用。不同於Windows 8的是[[代工生產|OEM商]]不需要將[[統一可延伸韌體介面#Secure_Boot|Secure Boot]]設置為用戶可配性，也就是說裝置或許可選性的鎖定運行於僅由微軟簽定的作業系統<ref name="arstechnica-securebootw10">{{Cite_web |title=Windows 10 to make the Secure Boot alt-OS lock out a reality |url=http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/03/windows-10-to-make-the-secure-boot-alt-os-lock-out-a-reality/ |website=Ars Technica |accessdate=2015-03-21 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150320210202/http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/03/windows-10-to-make-the-secure-boot-alt-os-lock-out-a-reality/ |archivedate=2015-03-20 }}</ref>。Windows Hello臉部識別認證功能需要使用受支援的紅外感光相機<ref name="ms-w10specs">{{Cite_web|title=Windows 10 specifications|url=https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/windows-10-specifications|publisher=Microsoft Corporation|accessdate=2015-06-03|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160810105826/https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/windows-10-specifications|archivedate=2016-08-10}}</ref>。Device Guard功能需要無第三方證書導入的UEFI系統，同時要求CPU虛擬化擴展功能（包括SLAT和IOMMU）和Secure Boot事先在韌體中開啟<ref name=ms-w10specs/>。

== 更新和支援 ==
{{Main|Windows 10版本历史}}
Windows 10的服务与以前版本的Windows有显著不同。由于其持续接收更新，微软将其称为“服务”，而泰瑞·麥爾森解释说，微软的目标是“你运行什么版本的Windows”的问题将不再有意义。<ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2015/01/windows-10-free-for-all-windows-8-1-and-windows-7-users-for-first-year/|title=Windows 10 free for all Windows 8.1 and 7 users for first year after release [Updated]|newspaper=Ars Technica|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126082632/http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2015/01/windows-10-free-for-all-windows-8-1-and-windows-7-users-for-first-year/|archivedate=2016-11-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/07/what-windows-as-a-service-and-a-free-upgrade-mean-at-home-and-at-work/|title=What Windows as a Service and a “free upgrade” mean at home and at work|newspaper=Ars Technica|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161217190827/http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/07/what-windows-as-a-service-and-a-free-upgrade-mean-at-home-and-at-work/|archivedate=2016-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_web|url=http://blogs.windows.com/windowsexperience/2015/01/21/the-next-generation-of-windows-windows-10/|title=The next generation of Windows: Windows 10|accessdate=2017-01-08|work=Windows Blogs|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101104227/https://blogs.windows.com/windowsexperience/2015/01/21/the-next-generation-of-windows-windows-10/|archivedate=2017-01-01}}</ref>

与以前版本的Windows不同，[[Windows_Update|Windows Update]]不允许选择性安装更新，并且自动下载并安装所有更新（包括补丁，功能更新和[[驱动程序|驱动程序]]）。<ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.cnet.com/how-to/windows-10-lets-you-schedule-windows-update-restarts/|title=Windows 10 lets you schedule Windows Update restarts|newspaper=CNET|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128030642/https://www.cnet.com/how-to/windows-10-lets-you-schedule-windows-update-restarts/|archivedate=2017-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.crn.com/news/applications-os/300077576/did-microsoft-just-backtrack-on-forced-updates-for-windows-10.htm%7Cwebsite=CRN.com|title=CRN Applications and OS News|newspaper=CRN|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108192146/http://www.crn.com/news/applications-os/300077576/did-microsoft-just-backtrack-on-forced-updates-for-windows-10.htm%7Cwebsite=CRN.com|archivedate=2017-01-08}}</ref>用户只能选择他们的系统是否会自动重新启动以在系统处于非活动状态时安装更新，或者通知计划重新启动。但是，如果通过[[WiFi|WiFi]]（而不是[[以太网|以太网]]）接收更新，则可以推迟下载更新，方法是将WiFi连接标记为按流量计费的（这也将减慢程序更新和文件同步）。更新可能会导致兼容性或其他问题；Microsoft故障排除程序允许卸载不良更新。Windows Update还可以使用对等系统分发更新；默认情况下，用户的带宽用于将以前下载的更新分发给其他用户，与Microsoft服务器结合使用，即“传递优化”。用户可以选择仅在其局域网内共享Windows更新<ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2953132/windows/set-windows-10s-wi-fi-connections-as-metered-to-download-forced-updates-at-your-own-pace.html|title=Set Windows 10's Wi-Fi connections as metered to download forced updates at your own pace|newspaper=PCWorld|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108005917/http://www.pcworld.com/article/2953132/windows/set-windows-10s-wi-fi-connections-as-metered-to-download-forced-updates-at-your-own-pace.html|archivedate=2017-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2975289/windows/how-to-cure-windows-10s-worst-headaches.html|title=How to cure Windows 10's worst headaches|newspaper=PCWorld|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202180516/http://www.pcworld.com/article/2975289/windows/how-to-cure-windows-10s-worst-headaches.html|archivedate=2017-02-02}}</ref>。

Windows 10的原始RTM版本（“Windows 10，于2015年7月发布”）在其最初发布之后的五年内获得主流支持，其后是五年的扩展支持，但这是受条件限制的。 Microsoft的操作系统支持生命周期策略提到“更新是累积的，每个更新构建在它之前的所有更新”，“设备需要安装最新更新以保持支持”，以及设备的能力接收未来更新将取决于硬件兼容性，驱动程序可用性，以及设备是否在OEM的“支持期”内 - 这是在以前版本的生命周期策略中未考虑的一个新方面。Microsoft最初表示，Windows 10将自由接收更新“支持的设备寿命”。<ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.computerworld.com/article/2949230/microsoft-windows/all-editions-of-windows-10-get-10-years-of-updates%7Cwork=Computerworld|title=All editions of Windows 10 get 10 years of updates, support|last=Keizer|first=Gregg|newspaper=Computerworld|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322223351/https://www.computerworld.com/article/2949230/microsoft-windows/all-editions-of-windows-10-get-10-years-of-updates%7Cwork=Computerworld|archivedate=2018-03-22}}</ref>为遵守美国会计法律，Windows 10的收入被推迟“在预期期间软件升级预计将由估计设备寿命提供”的直线基础上，定义为两到四年，取决于“客户类型”。 <ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2955491/windows/how-to-stop-windows-10-from-using-your-pcs-bandwidth-to-update-strangers-systems.html|title=How to stop Windows 10 from using your PC's bandwidth to update strangers' systems|newspaper=PCWorld|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108005921/http://www.pcworld.com/article/2955491/windows/how-to-stop-windows-10-from-using-your-pcs-bandwidth-to-update-strangers-systems.html|archivedate=2017-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.computerworld.com/article/2945796/microsoft-windows/microsoft-to-provide-free-upgrades-to-windows-10-for-2-to-4-years.html|title=Microsoft to provide free upgrades to Windows 10 for 2 to 4 years|last=Keizer|first=Gregg|newspaper=Computerworld|accessdate=2017-01-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129231620/http://www.computerworld.com/article/2945796/microsoft-windows/microsoft-to-provide-free-upgrades-to-windows-10-for-2-to-4-years.html|archivedate=2016-11-29}}</ref>

Windows 10接受服务的方式与之前的版本大相径庭，它會強制自動更新。泰瑞·麥爾森解释道：「微软的目的将淡化人们常论的『你用的Windows是哪个版本』，因此将以做为服务性的软件形式发放。」<ref name="ars-winasaservice">{{Cite_web |title=What Windows as a Service and a "free upgrade" mean at home and at work |url=http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/01/what-windows-as-a-service-and-a-free-upgrade-mean-at-home-and-at-work/ |website=Ars Technica |accessdate=2015-02-01 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131232902/http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/01/what-windows-as-a-service-and-a-free-upgrade-mean-at-home-and-at-work/ |archivedate=2015-01-31 }}</ref><ref name="ars-win10freefirstyear">{{Cite_web |title=Windows 10 free for all Windows 8.1 and Windows 7 users for first year |url=http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2015/01/windows-10-free-for-all-windows-8-1-and-windows-7-users-for-first-year/ |website=Ars Technica |accessdate=2015-01-21 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150121181443/http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2015/01/windows-10-free-for-all-windows-8-1-and-windows-7-users-for-first-year/ |archivedate=2015-01-21 }}</ref><ref name="ms-nextgen">{{Cite_web |last1=Myerson |first1=Terry |title=The next generation of Windows: Windows 10 |url=http://blogs.windows.com/bloggingwindows/2015/01/21/the-next-generation-of-windows-windows-10/ |website=Windows Blogs |publisher=Microsoft |accessdate=2015-01-21 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150121193023/http://blogs.windows.com/bloggingwindows/2015/01/21/the-next-generation-of-windows-windows-10/ |archivedate=2015-01-21 }}</ref>

不同于前些版本，Windows Update已经不允许有选择性的安装更新，而是所有更新一同強制性自动下载并安装，这其中包含补丁、功能性更新以及驱动程序。用户的選擇，只有在系统闲置时自动安装更新或通知以安排重新启动的時間點。<ref name="cnet-scheduleupdate">{{Cite_web|title=Windows 10 lets you schedule Windows Update restarts|url=http://www.cnet.com/how-to/windows-10-lets-you-schedule-windows-update-restarts/|website=CNET|accessdate=2015-08-04|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804081533/http://www.cnet.com/how-to/windows-10-lets-you-schedule-windows-update-restarts/|archivedate=2015-08-04}}</ref><ref name="crn-updates">{{Cite_web|title=Did Microsoft Just Backtrack On Forced Updates For Windows 10?|url=http://www.crn.com/news/applications-os/300077576/did-microsoft-just-backtrack-on-forced-updates-for-windows-10.htm|website=CRN.com|accessdate=2015-08-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805092314/http://www.crn.com/news/applications-os/300077576/did-microsoft-just-backtrack-on-forced-updates-for-windows-10.htm|archivedate=2015-08-05}}</ref>Windows Update也允许端对端（P2P）系统分发更新，這會佔掉用戶的頻寬，因此微軟讓這個功能可以關閉。默认情况下用户的带宽将配合微软服务器分发更新至其它用户电脑中；在局域网环境中用户可以单独使用端对端更新他们的电脑。<ref name="pcw-peertopeer">{{Cite_web|title=How to stop Windows 10 from using your PC's bandwidth to update strangers' systems|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2955491/windows/how-to-stop-windows-10-from-using-your-pcs-bandwidth-to-update-strangers-systems.html|website=PC World|publisher=IDG|accessdate=2015-08-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805145115/http://www.pcworld.com/article/2955491/windows/how-to-stop-windows-10-from-using-your-pcs-bandwidth-to-update-strangers-systems.html|archivedate=2015-08-05}}</ref>

